environments, Azure users"},"284":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-37","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#native","content":"Uses your platform's built-in speech recognition — Siri on Apple devices, Google Speech on Android. No setup required, works immediately. Accuracy depends on your platform's implementation, but it is solid for English and most major languages."},"285":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-38","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#whisper","content":"Runs OpenAI's Whisper model locally on your device. The first time you use it, Mate downloads the model (\\~150MB). After that, everything runs offline — no network requests, no API keys, no data leaving your machine."},"286":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-39","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#whisper","content":"Whisper handles accents and background noise well, and supports dozens of languages out of the box."},"287":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-40","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#cloud-stt","content":"Uses a cloud-based speech-to-text API for transcription. Requires an API key configured in Settings. Offers high accuracy and broad language support, with the tradeoff that audio is sent to an external service for processing."},"288":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-41","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#azure-speech","content":"Microsoft's Azure Speech Services. Requires an Azure subscription and speech resource key. A good fit if you are already in the Azure ecosystem or need enterprise-grade speech recognition with compliance guarantees."},"289":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-42","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#open-an-agent-chat-tab","content":"Voice input works in the agent chat composer — the text field where you type messages to the AI agent."},"290":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-43","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#tap-the-microphone-icon","content":"You will see a mic icon in the composer bar. Tap it to start recording. If this is your first time, Mate may ask for microphone permission."},"291":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-44","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#speak-your-message","content":"Talk naturally. The transcription appears in the composer as you speak. When you are done, tap the mic icon again to stop."},"292":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-45","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#review-and-send","content":"The transcribed text appears in the composer. Edit it if needed, then send it to the agent like any other message."},"293":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-46","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#choosing-an-engine","content":"Open **Settings** and look for the **Speech-to-Text** section. You can select your preferred engine and configure any required credentials. The engine selection persists across sessions."},"294":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-47","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#choosing-an-engine","content":"If you want fully offline voice input with no setup beyond the initial download, Whisper is the way to go. For zero-setup convenience, start with Native and switch later if you need better accuracy."},"295":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-48","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#language-support","content":"All four engines support multiple languages. The available languages depend on the engine:"},"296":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-49","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#language-support","content":"**Native**: Whatever your OS supports — typically 30+ languages on modern devices"},"297":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-50","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#language-support","content":"**Whisper**: 99 languages (full list on OpenAI's Whisper documentation)"},"298":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-51","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#language-support","content":"**Cloud STT**: Varies by provider, typically 50+ languages"},"299":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-52","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#language-support","content":"**Azure Speech**: 100+ languages and variants"},"300":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-53","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#language-support","content":"English variants (US, UK, Australian, etc.) are supported across all engines."},"301":{"id":"/docs/features/voice-input-54","page_id":"/docs/features/voice-input","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/voice-input#platform-availability","content":"Voice input works on all platforms where Mate runs: macOS, Windows, Linux, Android, and iOS. The Native engine uses platform-specific APIs, so the experience varies slightly — Siri's speech recognition on Apple devices, Google's on Android, and platform speech APIs on desktop. Whisper, Cloud STT, and Azure Speech behave identically across all platforms."},"302":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","type":"page","content":"Web Preview","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Features"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/features/web-preview"},"303":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-0","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview","content":"Preview localhost web apps from any paired device through a built-in reverse proxy."},"304":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-1","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/features/web-preview#how-it-works","content":"How it works"},"305":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-2","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/features/web-preview#opening-a-web-preview","content":"Opening a web preview"},"306":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-3","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/features/web-preview#use-cases","content":"Use cases"},"307":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-4","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/features/web-preview#live-reloading","content":"Live reloading"},"308":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-5","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/features/web-preview#limitations","content":"Limitations"},"309":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-6","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview","content":"Web Preview lets you view web applications running on one device from another device on your network. If your dev server is running on `localhost:3000` on your Mac, you can see it on your phone without any port forwarding or tunneling setup."},"310":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-7","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#how-it-works","content":"Mate runs a reverse proxy that forwards HTTP requests from the viewing device to the target device's localhost port. The web content is rendered in an embedded browser view within Mate."},"311":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-8","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#how-it-works","content":"This means:"},"312":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-9","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#how-it-works","content":"Your dev server runs normally on localhost"},"313":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-10","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#how-it-works","content":"Mate proxies requests through the paired connection"},"314":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-11","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#how-it-works","content":"The remote device sees the page as if it were on localhost"},"315":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-12","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#how-it-works","content":"No need to find your machine's IP address, no need to bind to `0.0.0.0`, no need for ngrok or similar tools."},"316":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-13","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#opening-a-web-preview","content":"Click &#x2A;*+** in the tab bar"},"317":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-14","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#opening-a-web-preview","content":"Select **Web Preview**"},"318":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-15","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#opening-a-web-preview","content":"Enter the port number (e.g., `3000`, `8080`, `5173`)"},"319":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-16","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#opening-a-web-preview","content":"The preview loads immediately if the server is running on that port."},"320":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-17","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#use-cases","content":"**Mobile testing**: Preview your web app on your actual phone while developing on your desktop"},"321":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-18","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#use-cases","content":"**Cross-device review**: Show a teammate the app running on your machine by having them pair their device"},"322":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-19","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#use-cases","content":"**Remote monitoring**: Check on a running dev server or dashboard from your phone"},"323":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-20","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#use-cases","content":"Web Preview works for any HTTP server running on localhost — React dev servers, Next.js, Vite, Express, Django, Rails, or anything else that serves over HTTP."},"324":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-21","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#live-reloading","content":"If your dev server supports hot module replacement (HMR) or live reload, it works through the preview. Changes you make in your editor trigger the same automatic refresh you would see in a local browser."},"325":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-22","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#limitations","content":"WebSocket connections through the proxy depend on your server's WebSocket configuration"},"326":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-23","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#limitations","content":"HTTPS localhost servers may require additional setup"},"327":{"id":"/docs/features/web-preview-24","page_id":"/docs/features/web-preview","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/features/web-preview#limitations","content":"The embedded browser view has standard web rendering capabilities but is not a full desktop browser"},"328":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","type":"page","content":"First Session","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Getting Started"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/first-session"},"329":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session-0","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","content":"Open your first terminal session and learn basic navigation in Mate."},"330":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session-1","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/first-session#the-workspace","content":"The workspace"},"331":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session-2","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/first-session#open-a-terminal","content":"Open a terminal"},"332":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session-3","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/first-session#working-with-tabs","content":"Working with tabs"},"333":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session-4","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/first-session#tab-types-at-a-glance","content":"Tab types at a glance"},"334":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session-5","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/first-session#try-an-ai-agent","content":"Try an AI agent"},"335":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session-6","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/first-session#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"336":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session-7","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/first-session","tags":[],"type":"text","