orm","content":"Download the `.tar.gz` file from the releases page"},"411":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-36","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Extract it: `tar xzf mate-linux-*.tar.gz`"},"412":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-37","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Run the `mate` binary from the extracted folder"},"413":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-38","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#install-by-platform","content":"Node.js is bundled with the app"},"414":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-39","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#mobile-apps","content":"iOS and Android apps are available for pairing with a desktop running Mate. Mobile devices act as remote mirrors — they connect to your desktop over the local network and let you interact with your sessions from your phone or tablet."},"415":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-40","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#mobile-apps","content":"Mobile devices do not run terminals or AI agents locally. They connect to a paired desktop that does the heavy lifting. See Pairing Devices for setup instructions."},"416":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-41","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#verify-the-installation","content":"After launching Mate, you should see the workspace with a default terminal tab. Try typing a command to confirm everything works:"},"417":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/installation-42","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/installation#verify-the-installation","content":"If the terminal responds, you are good to go. Head to First Session to learn the basics."},"418":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"page","content":"Pairing Devices","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Getting Started"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices"},"419":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-0","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","content":"Pair your phone or another computer with Mate over your local network."},"420":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-1","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#how-pairing-works","content":"How pairing works"},"421":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-2","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#launch-mate-on-both-devices","content":"Launch Mate on both devices"},"422":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-3","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#wait-for-discovery","content":"Wait for discovery"},"423":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-4","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#tap-to-pair","content":"Tap to pair"},"424":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-5","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"What paired devices can do"},"425":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-6","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#network-requirements","content":"Network requirements"},"426":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-7","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#troubleshooting-pairing","content":"Troubleshooting pairing"},"427":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-8","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#multiple-devices","content":"Multiple devices"},"428":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-9","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","content":"Mate lets you access your desktop sessions from any device on the same network. Your desktop is the server — it runs the terminals, AI agents, and editors. Paired devices are live mirrors that connect directly, with no cloud involved."},"429":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-10","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#how-pairing-works","content":"Mate uses multicast UDP for automatic device discovery on your local network. When two devices running Mate are on the same Wi-Fi or LAN, they find each other automatically. No manual IP entry, no account creation, no cloud relay."},"430":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-11","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#launch-mate-on-both-devices","content":"Open Mate on your desktop and on the device you want to pair (phone, tablet, or another computer)."},"431":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-12","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#wait-for-discovery","content":"Devices on the same network appear automatically in the sidebar within a few seconds. You will see the other device's name show up under the device list."},"432":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-13","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#tap-to-pair","content":"Select the discovered device in the sidebar. The first connection establishes the pairing. Once paired, the device remembers the connection for future sessions."},"433":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-14","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Once paired, the remote device can:"},"434":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-15","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"View and interact with all terminal sessions running on the desktop"},"435":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-16","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Chat with AI agents that are running on the desktop"},"436":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-17","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Browse and edit files through the IDE"},"437":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-18","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Preview web apps running on the desktop's localhost"},"438":{"id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices-19","page_id":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/getting-started/pairing-devices#what-paired-devices-can-do","content":"Send and receive files"},